motion-world is an independent, provider-agnostic skill.

Its workflow is inspired in part by oso95/scroll-world, especially these ideas:
- maintain one visual style across generated scenes;
- use actual rendered boundary frames when chaining video clips;
- prepare mobile-specific output instead of blindly cropping desktop output;
- drive motion by a normalized scroll/progress value;
- use short GOP encodes for responsive seeking.

scroll-world is MIT licensed. Upstream repository:
https://github.com/oso95/scroll-world

No upstream source code is required at runtime. Review the upstream license when
copying upstream files or substantial portions into another distribution.
